description.p:
According to a second aspect, the present invention also relates to a method for limiting the retraction speed of a belt arranged on a belt reel. The belt reel is adapted for a vehicle safety restraint arrangement, the method comprising the steps of;
retracting the belt onto a belt reel using a retraction mechanism;
limiting the maximum speed during the retraction by imparting a braking force to the belt reel using induction.

Non limiting embodiment of the present invention will be described in greater details with reference to the following figures in which;
figure 1 shows a driver of a car, the driver being buckled up using a belt, buckle and a belt reel according to an embodiment of the present invention;
figure 2 shows the belt reel of figure 1 in greater detail;
figure 3 shows the belt reel of figure 3 in a cross section;
figure 4 shows the belt reel of figure 3 in a cross section;
figure 5 shows a belt reel according to the present invention in a cross section having an alternative belt retraction brake;
figure 6 shows the belt reel of figure 5 in a cross section;
figure 7 shows a diagram of a the highest spot speed vs number for; a belt reel without induction brake and; a belt reel comprising induction brake and a strengthened retraction mechanism in the form of a strengthened spring and;
figures 8a-8b show a schematic embodiment of a belt retraction brake in two different views.

The diagram of figure 7 is further partitioned in three areas;

the first area represents damage to pillars and doors, and primarily the A-pillar of the car; the second area represents a state at which no damage occurs, i.e. the belt is retracted without any damages or negative consequences and;

the third area represents damage to the belt web, buckle, door seal, or the lacquer in the door area of the car.

claim.claim-text:
A method for limiting the retraction speed of a belt (14) arranged on a belt reel (20), the belt reel (20) being adapted for a vehicle safety restraint arrangement, said method comprising the steps of;
- retracting the belt (14) onto a belt reel (20) using a retraction mechanism;
- limiting the maximum speed during the retraction by imparting a braking force to the belt reel (20) using induction.
